INmanage Fair Commercial License (FCL)
Version 1.0 – January 2026

Copyright (c) 2026 INmanage contributors

1. Purpose

This license is designed to allow free use of INmanage while ensuring
fair and sustainable usage in professional and commercial environments.

It is based on trust and professional responsibility rather than
technical enforcement.

2. Permitted Use

INmanage may be used free of charge in private, internal, evaluation,
and commercial contexts.

3. Commercial Use

Commercial use is permitted. Supporting the project with a Commercial
Support License is appreciated and considered best practice.

Commercial use includes, but is not limited to:

- Offering INmanage as part of paid services
- Using INmanage in client projects
- Internal use within a for-profit organization
- Managed hosting, maintenance, or provisioning services
- Operating INmanage for third parties for compensation

Supporting the project provides legal clarity for such usage.

4. Commercial Support License

A Commercial Support License is obtained by financially supporting the
project via the official support channels.

The license:
- Is voluntary and not technically enforced
- Does not require a license key at this stage
- Is based on professional fairness and good faith
- Can be one-off or recurring, at your discretion

Details are described in LICENSING.md.

5. Redistribution and Modification

You may modify and redistribute INmanage, provided that:

- This license text remains included
- The origin of the software is not misrepresented
- Modifications are clearly marked

Redistribution does not alter the support model described above.

6. No DRM, No Call-Home

INmanage does not include DRM, license enforcement, or mandatory
call-home mechanisms.

Any future telemetry or enforcement mechanisms will be documented
clearly and transparently and will not be retroactively applied.

7. Warranty and Liability

INmanage is provided "AS IS", without warranty of any kind.

In no event shall the authors or contributors be liable for any claim,
damages, or other liability arising from the use of the software.

8. Future Licensing Model Changes

The authors reserve the right to offer INmanage under additional or
alternative licenses in the future, including:

- Open-source licenses
- Dual licensing models
- Commercial licenses

Such changes will:
- Not retroactively affect versions already released under this license
- Not invalidate previously granted usage rights
- Be clearly documented at the time of change

9. Acceptance

By using, copying, modifying, or distributing INmanage, you agree to
the terms of this license.
